President Barack Obama has proclaimed June 2016 as African-American Music Appreciation Month. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of African-American music as a vital part of American heritage and its ability to bring people together and inspire them. He emphasizes that African-American music reflects the human experience and resonates with people from all walks of life. The proclamation calls upon public officials, educators, and all Americans to observe the month with activities and programs that raise awareness and foster appreciation of music composed, arranged, or performed by African-Americans.